Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.66,0:00:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut cases are even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.54,0:00:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.88,0:00:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is the pottery\Ncase solution!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.55,0:00:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are no cracks\Nin Conan's logic!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.48,0:00:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single\Ntruth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.36,0:00:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.21,0:00:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.01,0:01:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kikuemon-{\i1}san{\i0}, a potter and\Nliving national treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.80,0:01:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,invited me, Ran, and the old\Nguy to his home in West Tama.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.97,0:02:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before long,\Nan incident occurred!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.28,0:02:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Masuko-{\i1}san {\i0}broke Kikuemon-{\i1}san{\i0}'s\Nlatest work, the {\i1}Fusui-maru{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.86,0:02:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That night, during a get-together,\NMasuko-{\i1}san {\i0}became very drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.74,0:02:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The following\Nmorning in the storeroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...she was hanged to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.33,0:02:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Famous Potter Murder Case (Part 2)."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.17,0:02:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you really all\Ntogether in the stateroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.17,0:02:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes. The only one who left\Nwas Otani, who went to wake her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.05,0:02:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.94,0:02:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.64,0:02:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you pretended to\Nwake her and hung her in her sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.23,0:02:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! I was only gone for a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.04,0:02:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her room is only two\Nover from the stateroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.32,0:02:55.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.58,0:02:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.57,0:02:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he was gone\Nfor less than ten seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.82,0:03:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't have done\Nanything in such a short time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.54,0:03:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone else leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.75,0:03:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I left for a\Nshort moment to call her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.08,0:03:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought she\Nhad gone somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.75,0:03:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't really leave, though;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.43,0:03:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only called her cell phone from\Nthe phone in the connecting hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.93,0:03:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. She's not answering.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.85,0:03:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cell phone? Hers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.85,0:03:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I had Masuko-{\i1}san\N{\i0}always carry a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.70,0:03:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was in charge of everything else,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.95,0:03:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that we could focus\Non making our works.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.77,0:03:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is "everything else"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.78,0:03:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Things like business transactions\Nand scheduling exhibitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.50,0:03:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So our master very rarely goes anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.81,0:03:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's odd. We didn't\Nfind a cell phone by her body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.79,0:03:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, a cell phone was\Nfound in the victim's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:04:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was apparently under her futon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.67,0:04:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under her futon?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.60,0:04:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She always put it under her\Npillow and used it as an alarm clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.60,0:04:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cell phone\Nwas apparently turned off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.44,0:04:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's why a call from just\Nthe other room wouldn't be heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, did anyone else leave the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.66,0:04:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no one else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.67,0:04:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.69,0:04:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I know of.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.16,0:04:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who could have carried\Nher in here and killed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.63,0:04:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming she was found\Nright after she was hanged,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.80,0:04:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone has an alibi\Nof being in the stateroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.79,0:04:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I'm saying!\NIt was a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.52,0:04:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her feet were bare because she\Nwas upset and about to kill herself,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.35,0:04:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and her feet weren't dirty because\Nshe used the stepping stones
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.32,0:04:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,between the house\Nand the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.50,0:05:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, she had broken the\N{\i1}Fusui-maru {\i0}in this storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.69,0:05:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can imagine her seeing\Nthe storeroom when she woke up
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and walking in without too much thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.16,0:05:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true. The rope was used\Nin this storeroom for packing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.88,0:05:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus we all heard the pot\Nbreak at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.55,0:05:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, we won't make any progress
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.55,0:05:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until we examine the\Nstoreroom in more detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.43,0:05:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ask that you all wait in the\Nstateroom for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.10,0:05:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't do\Nanything without permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.07,0:05:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide? Is that really what it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.32,0:05:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, too many things\Nare out of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.82,0:05:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The open cut on her right leg...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.41,0:05:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her unusual lack of footwear\Nand the clean bottoms of her feet...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.24,0:05:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.09,0:05:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this marble I found by the broken\N{\i1}Fusui-maru {\i0}the day before...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.92,0:06:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what's the other thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.13,0:06:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something I saw at the\Nscene of the crime is bugging me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.10,0:06:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.35,0:06:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just a marble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.30,0:06:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only kids would be\Ninterested in junk like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.56,0:06:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.99,0:06:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.53,0:06:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! What the--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.82,0:06:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Where do\Nyou think you're going?! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.04,0:06:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.74,0:06:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lipstick?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.88,0:06:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't put it there...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.47,0:06:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is lipstick doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.59,0:06:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.80,0:06:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.72,0:06:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait! S-Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.72,0:06:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.94,0:06:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing that bugged me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.60,0:06:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.49,0:07:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.81,0:07:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.28,0:07:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe so, but you\Ncan't just barge in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.99,0:07:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's the lady's body?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.86,0:07:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taken to the police hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.89,0:07:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.50,0:07:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally found a trace\Nthat the killer failed to hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact it's here\Nmeans that up above is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.51,0:07:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.86,0:07:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this method, you wouldn't\Nneed to be in the room to kill her!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.19,0:07:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But to ensure she would die,\Nit would have to be around there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.07,0:07:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.50,0:07:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! What are you doing! Come down!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.69,0:07:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I'm looking\Nfor something I forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.00,0:08:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just checked that area,\Nbut there was nothing out of the ordinary!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.88,0:08:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now come down! It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.05,0:08:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Doesn't seem to\Nbe anything but pottery here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.81,0:08:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting! That's a potter for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come down this minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.02,0:08:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.24,0:08:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means one\Nof those two is the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.90,0:08:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but it's probably that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.25,0:08:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He laid a trap for her and killed\Nher to make it look like a suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.58,0:08:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And only he would\Nstill have proof of it on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.59,0:08:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! I know who did it and how!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.46,0:08:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The question now is\Nhow to tell Inspector Megure...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.27,0:08:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, how long do we\Nhave to stay in the stateroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.81,0:09:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry!\NWe'll still be a little while longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.39,0:09:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could we get something to eat?\NWe haven't eaten at all today...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.69,0:09:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to change clothes, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that should be fine,\Nas long as you tell my men first!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.62,0:09:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! If they do that,\Nthe evidence'll be gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.62,0:09:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.29,0:09:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, you stupid kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.62,0:09:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.59,0:09:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Evidence, my butt! This was\Na suicide! There was no killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.30,0:09:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.21,0:09:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.67,0:09:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.43,0:09:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll just have to knock him\Nout with this stun-gun wristwatch...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say! I found the thing\Nyou were talking about earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.48,0:09:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.07,0:09:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't care if I say it\Nout loud for everyone to hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.77,0:09:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.82,0:09:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.94,0:09:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I was saying,\Nearlier, you told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.71,0:10:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'll just put the\Nbutton speaker on his collar...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.38,0:10:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You found it! Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.80,0:10:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on. Just what did you find?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.89,0:10:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Evidence that the killer failed\Nto hide completely, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.97,0:10:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Killer?! Are you saying--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.18,0:10:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She didn't commit\Nsuicide at all. She was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.02,0:10:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By someone here, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.49,0:10:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! This should be interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.49,0:10:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor to watch the great\NSleeping Kogoro at work firsthand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.32,0:10:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}! If the body\Nwas found right after she died,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.29,0:10:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,these people couldn't\Npossibly have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, you were the one\Nwho insisted it was a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.21,0:10:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a lie meant\Nto throw the killer off guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.26,0:10:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because we wouldn't want the\Nevidence to be destroyed, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.38,0:11:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again, just what is this evidence?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.01,0:11:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blood, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.30,0:11:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.26,0:11:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Kogoro-{\i1}ojisan {\i0}asked me to\Nlook for strange blood on the floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.56,0:11:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.94,0:11:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? He must've meant blood like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.69,0:11:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.32,0:11:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You carried the body over here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.87,0:11:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We thought she might still be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.58,0:11:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had her arms and Seto had her legs
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.62,0:11:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when we set her down in the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.93,0:11:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.76,0:11:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.68,0:11:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then this really is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.76,0:11:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the deal with that blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.93,0:11:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think blood dripped from\Nthe body when we were carrying it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.14,0:11:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not all of the blood was from then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.27,0:11:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to tell, since\Nit's mixed with other blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.28,0:11:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's something else here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.65,0:11:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.03,0:12:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The shape that drops\Nof human blood make
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.03,0:12:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is pretty much determined\Nby how far they fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.25,0:12:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The farther the fall,\Nthe larger the circle,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.08,0:12:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the more developed\Nthe surrounding splatter is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.20,0:12:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had carried\Nher by her arms and legs,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.34,0:12:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the distance from her toenails\Nto the floor was 50 cm at best.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.05,0:12:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, these blood drops\Nclearly fell more than a meter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.63,0:12:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that such blood is here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.85,0:12:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying she\Nwas on top of this shelf?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.68,0:12:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.90,0:12:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.06,0:12:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The killer had carried her\Nto the top of the shelf last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.50,0:12:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...where she slept, with a rope around\Nher neck, tied to the roof beam.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.54,0:12:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way, when she woke in the morning,\Nshe would lose her balance,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.71,0:12:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,fall from the shelf,\Nand wind up hanging herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.08,0:13:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The loud sound right\Nafter she was hanged
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.63,0:13:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was from the pots\Nleft directly below the noose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.31,0:13:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being hanged from that height\Nwould result in an almost instant death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.48,0:13:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The broken pots would then look\Nlike a stepstool she had overturned.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.44,0:13:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, this was also meant\Nto hasten the body's discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.45,0:13:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and solidify the alibi of\Nthe killer inside the stateroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.78,0:13:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about\Nthe cut on her right calf?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.41,0:13:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look closely at the top of the shelf.\NDo you see a protruding nail?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.71,0:13:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.71,0:13:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When she lost her balance and fell,\Nshe likely cut her calf on that nail.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.68,0:13:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blood landed on a\Ndifferent spot on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.31,0:13:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,probably because she had held\Non to the shelf for a few seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.82,0:13:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning she just happened\Nto get the cut on her calf?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.23,0:14:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It wasn't part of the killer's plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.70,0:14:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was probably quite\Nshocked when he saw her cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.33,0:14:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the killer would've quickly\Ndiscovered the cause of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.08,0:14:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as the blood right by the shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.92,0:14:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the body swung, the shelf\Nwould still have been too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.71,0:14:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fearing his trick would be\Nfigured out if this blood was found,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.01,0:14:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer directed the others\Ncarrying her body to the blood
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.31,0:14:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to try to hide it with new blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.90,0:14:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, the one\Nwho left last night's party
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.90,0:14:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to carry her to the storeroom\Nand set up this trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.41,0:14:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Seto Ryuichi-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Seto?! Don't tell me it was you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.91,0:14:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, now! I wasn't the\Nonly one who left during the party!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.04,0:15:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, why would\NI do something so daring
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.89,0:15:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with a great detective\Nlike you around?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.26,0:15:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.01,0:15:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because she had\Nbroken the {\i1}Fusui-maru{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.76,0:15:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it you who put a\Nmarble under the {\i1}Fusui-maru{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.85,0:15:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it easy to fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.81,0:15:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To make this murder look\Nlike a suicide that she committed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because of her own\Nmishandling of things?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.78,0:15:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.32,0:15:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she was in charge\Nof selling these works,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.49,0:15:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she would've been the one\Nwho stored and removed them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.33,0:15:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she was bound\Nto drop it eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.03,0:15:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, she fell\Nasleep drunk during the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.92,0:15:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last night was the perfect chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.43,0:15:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please knock this off! You shouldn't\Nblame me without any proof...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.68,0:15:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I believe\Nyou're still wearing the proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.27,0:15:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, Inspector!\NPlease lift up the back of his jacket!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.49,0:16:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.90,0:16:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lipstick?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.40,0:16:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That most likely got there while\Nyou were carrying her up the shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.00,0:16:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd have to carry her on your\Nshoulders to use the ladder, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you returned to the stateroom,\Nas if nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.28,0:16:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had left the party to carry\Nher here before she sobered up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.17,0:16:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a look at the sitting\Ncushions in the stateroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.06,0:16:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One has a bit of the lipstick\Nhe brought back with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.51,0:16:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, now!\NYes, this might be her lipstick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.53,0:16:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe she just\Nhappened to touch my back
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.24,0:16:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while she was\Nsleeping during the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.08,0:16:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was drunk last night,\Nso I don't really remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.20,0:16:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but can you say\Nthat isn't a possibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.33,0:16:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.66,0:17:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You leave me no choice then.\NI'll show my trump card.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.42,0:17:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan!\NShow 'em what you found.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.88,0:17:10.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.88,0:17:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.46,0:17:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! That's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.10,0:17:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.53,0:17:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.32,0:17:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A cell phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.15,0:17:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this doing inside a pot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.07,0:17:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To make sure this murder\Nworked as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.79,0:17:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if she was atop a narrow shelf,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.58,0:17:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there'd be no guarantee\Nshe'd lose her balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.58,0:17:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it'd be a different story\Nif a phone under her pillow rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.91,0:17:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that situation, most people\Nwould reach out without thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.21,0:17:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even more so if she used\Nher cell phone as an alarm clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.88,0:18:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Seto-{\i1}san {\i0}placed that\Npot in the shelf directly under her
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.97,0:18:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and had the cell phone in this\Nspecial double-bottomed pot ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.19,0:18:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Checking the cell phone's\Nnumber should make it immediately clear
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.62,0:18:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that it belongs to Seto-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.17,0:18:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, detective.\NHow did you know it was me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.14,0:18:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I made the call. But Otani\Ncould have too when he left the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.51,0:18:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.55,0:18:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so too when Conan\Nfound the pot with the phone in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.47,0:18:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.69,0:18:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, when you tried\Nto call her, you said this:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.87,0:18:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. She's not answering.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.91,0:19:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But her cell phone had\Nbeen turned off when it was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.53,0:19:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cell phone was\Napparently turned off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In such cases,\Na cell phone would reply
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.79,0:19:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by saying that it is either\Nturned off or out of signal range.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.05,0:19:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My suspicion was confirmed\Nonce I remembered that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.01,0:19:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My suspicion that when you called,\Nyou called a different number.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.06,0:19:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I guess I should've said\NI couldn't get through to her phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.90,0:19:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't believe you'd destroy\NMaster's {\i1}Fusui-maru {\i0}to kill her!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.99,0:19:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That thing can turn\Nto dust for all I care.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.99,0:19:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it's a counterfeit\Ncopy I made of the real {\i1}Fusui-maru{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.00,0:19:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Counterfeit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.25,0:19:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The real one is\Nstored in a different location.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.63,0:20:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, even though it broke,\Nto think I could fool even her eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.77,0:20:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My skill has really come far.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.02,0:20:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though that's why she sold\Nmy works for high prices, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.28,0:20:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-High prices?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.97,0:20:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.28,0:20:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.07,0:20:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She took my works and sold\Nthem to rich, artistic know-nothings,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.21,0:20:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,claiming they were Master's works!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.12,0:20:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.12,0:20:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the time I realized it,\Nshe had already sold several dozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.26,0:20:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I questioned her about it, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.80,0:20:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but she not only didn't apologize...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.13,0:20:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be thankful\Nmore than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.34,0:20:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually selling the\Nunoriginal junk that you make!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.02,0:20:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, does that mean\Nyour recent slump was--?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.48,0:20:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! It was on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.86,0:21:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to harm\NMaster's name any further...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.54,0:21:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she threatened to kick\Nme out if I didn't keep making stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't put\Nup with it anymore, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.83,0:21:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.72,0:21:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell\NMaster about it?! Surely he--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.52,0:21:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.44,0:21:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't tell him my fakes sold\Nfor more than his authentic works...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.41,0:21:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.51,0:23:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! So that's the\Ncup worth 10 million yen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.89,0:23:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. It doesn't\Nseem that valuable to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.31,0:23:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appearances don't always\Nmatch what's on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.40,0:23:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.65,0:23:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.75,0:23:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In his case, his appearance does\Nmatch what's on the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.41,0:24:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First love?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.56,0:24:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.58,0:24:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asami-{\i1}senpai{\i0} was Shinichi's first love?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.60,0:24:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The villa is on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.49,0:24:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.66,0:24:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she's still inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.41,0:24:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asami-{\i1}senpai{\i0} is still inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.84,0:24:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Senpai{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.89,0:24:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan: "The Memories of\NFirst Love Case (Part 1)."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.09,0:24:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.52,0:24:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lemon pie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.65,0:24:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does your first love taste like?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.59,0:24:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eel bowls.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.97,0:24:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.76,0:24:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
